Reasoning: The paper deals with beamforming on a multiple-input-single-output interference channel with interference decoding capability, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses different decoding structures and characterizes the Pareto boundary, which falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SI). The use of multiple antennas and beamforming also relates to multimedia systems (cs.MM) and communication engineering (cs.CE).
